\section{General information on the datasets}\label{chap:basic-info}

The general information on the datasets is shown in Table \ref{tab:bi}. The column \textit{Graphs} shows the number of graphs in the dataset, \textit{Classes} shows the number of classes, \textit{Avg. Nodes} shows the average number of nodes in the graphs, \textit{Avg. Edges} shows the average number of edges in the graphs, and \textit{Category} shows the category of the dataset.

\pagebreak

\section{Graph parameters}\label{chap:graph-parameters}

The graph parameters for the datasets are presented in Table \ref{tab:gp1} and Table \ref{tab:gp2}. The columns in these tables represent the following metrics: \textit{DEG} (average degree), \textit{ASP} (average shortest path), \textit{DIA} (graph diameter), \textit{DEN} (graph density), \textit{GCC} (graph clustering coefficient), \textit{ACC} (average closeness centrality), \textit{ABC} (average betweenness centrality), \textit{AEC} (average eigenvector centrality), and \textit{WLC} (1-WL color count).

Some graph parameters are taking only the values zero or one. This occurs because certain datasets exclusively consist of fully connected graphs.
